FR940325-2-00039 FR940325-2-00016 Environment, Safety and Health Advisory Committee; Open Meeting AGENCY: Department of Energy. ACTION: Notice of open meeting. SUMMARY: Pursuant to the provisions of the Federal Advisory Committee Act (Pub. L. No. 92&hyph;463, 86 Stat. 770), notice is hereby given of the following meeting: DATE AND TIME: April 13, 1994, 9 a.m.&hyph;4 p.m. April 14, 1994, 9 a.m.&hyph;3:30 p.m. PLACE: The Key Bridge Marriott Hotel, 1401 Lee Highway, Arlington, Virginia 22209. FOR FURTHER INFORMATION CONTACT: Geoffrey Judge, Designated Federal Official, or Loretta Young, U.S. Department of Energy, Office of Environment, Safety and Health, EH&hyph;1, room 7A&hyph;097, Washington, DC 20585, Telephone: 202/586&hyph;6151. SUPPLEMENTARY INFORMATION: Purpose of the Committee: To provide advice and guidance to the Department of Energy (DOE) on matters relating to environment, safety and health at DOE facilities. Tentative Agenda Wednesday, April 13, 1994 9&hyph;9:05␣Call to Order, Geoffrey Judge, Designated Federal Official. 9:05&hyph;9:30␣Opening Remarks and General Business, Ellen Mangione, Acting Chair. 9:30&hyph;10␣Update on the Office of Environment, Safety and Health, Tara O'Toole, Assistant Secretary for Environment, Safety and Health, DOE. 10&hyph;10:15␣Break. 10:15&hyph;11:15␣Health and Human Services Advisory Committee, John Bagby. 11:15&hyph;11:45␣Environment, Safety and Health Strategic Planning, Tara O'Toole, DOE. 11:45&hyph;1␣Lunch. 1&hyph;2␣Environment, Safety and Health Vulnerability Studies, Mark Williams and Sarbes Acharya, DOE. 2&hyph;2:45␣Accountability for Management of Environment, Safety and Health Programs, Frank Tooper, DOE. 2:45&hyph;3␣Break. 3&hyph;4␣Public Input and Public Comment_10 minute rule. 4␣Meeting Adjourned. Thursday, April 14, 1994 9&hyph;9:15␣Opening Remarks, Ellen Mangione, Acting Chair. 9:15&hyph;10␣International Health Studies, Harry Pettengill, DOE. 10&hyph;11␣Medical Surveillance Program, Heather Stockwell, DOE. 11&hyph;11:15␣Break. 11:15&hyph;12:30␣Report on Radiation Control Subcommittee, John Poston, Texas A&M University. 12:30&hyph;1:30␣Lunch. 1:30&hyph;2:30␣Radiation Protection, Rick Jones, DOE. 2:30&hyph;2:45␣Future Meeting. 2:45&hyph;3␣Closing Remarks and Adjournment. Public Participation: The meeting is open to the public. The Acting Chairperson is empowered to conduct the meeting in a fashion that will facilitate the orderly conduct of business. Any member of the public who wishes to file a written statement with the Committee will be permitted to do so, either or after the meeting. Members of the public who wish to make oral statements pertaining to agenda items should contact Loretta Young at the address or telephone number listed above. Requests must be received at least five business days prior to the meeting and reasonable provisions will be made to include the presentation on the agenda. Persons wishing to attend the public meeting should provide their names to Loretta Young at (202) 586&hyph;6151 by April 6, 1994. Transcript: Available for public review and copying at the Public Reading Room, room 1E&hyph;190, Forrestal Building, 1000 Independence Avenue, SW., Washington, DC, between 9 a.m. and 4 p.m., Monday through Friday, except Federal holidays. Issued at Washington, DC, on March 22, 1994. Marcia L. Morris, Deputy Advisory Committee, Management Officer. [FR Doc. 94&hyph;7111 Filed 3&hyph;24&hyph;94; 8:45 am] BILLING CODE 6450&hyph;01&hyph;M
